<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08056g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08056g">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08056g"> 56(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> stolen 1006 / found in bog &mdash; gold cover</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">in the year 1006 &hellip; &ldquo;the large Gospel of Colum Cille&rdquo; in its cover of gold studded with precious stones, &ldquo;the chief relic of the western world,&rdquo; was stolen by night from the greater church at Kells, and found, after a lapse of some months, concealed under sods, destitute of its gold-covered binding. <small> Sir Edward Sullivan, <a name="BOK1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BOK1"><cite title="source">The Book of Kells</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (1920) 3/4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
